  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Sixty four participants were enrolled in a randomized, controlled clinical trial to evaluate
      the effectiveness of daily cane use on pain, function, quality of life and energy consumption
      during the gait in patients with knee osteoarthritis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Treatment, Randomized, Single Blind, Parallel Assignment, Efficacy Study
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
